Sentencas: Effects of thermal cycling on the formation of oxide scales were investigated in FeCr alloy interconnects for solid oxide fuel cells.
Titulo: Effects of Thermal Cycling on the Formation of Oxide Scale of Fe-Cr Alloy Interconnects for Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: Thermal cycling between 293 and 1073 K with a heating rate of 250 K/h was examined.
Titulo: Effects of Thermal Cycling on the Formation of Oxide Scale of Fe-Cr Alloy Interconnects for Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: Relatively large oxide scale grains were formed on the surface.
Titulo: Effects of Thermal Cycling on the Formation of Oxide Scale of Fe-Cr Alloy Interconnects for Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: These grains mainly consisted of the spinel-based oxides formed by fast diffusion of Mn along the grain boundaries of the FeCr alloy.
Titulo: Effects of Thermal Cycling on the Formation of Oxide Scale of Fe-Cr Alloy Interconnects for Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: Although the oxide scale/alloy interface showed strong contact without exfoliation, some cracks were found at the oxide scale surface.
Titulo: Effects of Thermal Cycling on the Formation of Oxide Scale of Fe-Cr Alloy Interconnects for Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: The elemental distribution in the oxide scale was similar to that of samples with the normal annealing (without thermal cycling).
Titulo: Effects of Thermal Cycling on the Formation of Oxide Scale of Fe-Cr Alloy Interconnects for Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: The growth of oxide scale was promoted by thermal cycling especially at the grain boundary of the FeCr alloy, which eventually resulted in the formation of a thick oxide scale.
Titulo: Effects of Thermal Cycling on the Formation of Oxide Scale of Fe-Cr Alloy Interconnects for Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: An increase of oxide-scale growth rates with the thermal cycling was evaluated taking into account microstructures and elemental distributions.
Titulo: Effects of Thermal Cycling on the Formation of Oxide Scale of Fe-Cr Alloy Interconnects for Solid Oxide Fuel Cells
